cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.LO, cs.CG. 

The paper deals with enumeration complexity classes and parametrised function classes, which are topics typically studied in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of exponent slices and the connection to classical enumeration collapse suggest a possible connection to computational geometry (cs.CG). The study of hierarchies and the definition of new classes also suggest a possible connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and combinatorics (cs.DS). Finally, the use of parametrised functions and the connection to TFNP suggest a possible connection to logic and computation (cs.LO).
